<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964777>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17.Scanning electronmicrographs forvarious phyline taxa.A. Acrorrhinium inexpectatum Josifov,head and pronotum. B. Cleotomiris miyamotoiYasunaga, pretarsal structure of metaleg.C. Hallodapus centrimaculatus (Poppius), same. D−F. Stridulatory device of H. brunneus (Poppius, 1915) (D: edge of forewing, or exocorium and F: dorsal metafemur). G. Harpocera orientalis Kerzhner, male antennomere II. H. Same, pretarsal structure of metaleg. I. Decomia cephalotes Poppius, same. J. Campylomma lividicorne Reuter, metafemur. K. Atractotomus morio J. Sahlberg, apical metafemur. L. Kasumiphylus kyushuensis (Linnavuori), same. M. Lasiolabops cirratus Yasunaga & Duwal, embolium and thoracic pleura, left lateral view. N. Same, pretarsal structure of metaleg. O. Pilophorus typicus (Distant), same. Abbreviations—cw: claw, pp: parempodium, pv: pulvillus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964777/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964787>
    dc:description "FIGURE 21. Scanning electron micrographs for Europiella isodonicola n. sp. (A−F), E. miyamotoi (G−L), E. lividella (M−N) and E. senjoensis (O). A, G, M. Left lateral habitus. B, H. Head, dorsal view. C, I. Thoracic pleura, left lateral view. D, J. Metafemur, ventral view. E−F, K−L. Metatarsus. N. Male genital segment. O. Corium." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964787/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964761>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Habitus images of Orthonotus spp. A−C, H. O. nakagawai n. sp. D–E. O. takaii n. sp. F–G. O. bicoloripes (from Primorsky, FE Russia). A, D, E, F, H. Male. B, G. Female. C. Fifth instar nymph. Images courtesy of Y. Nakagawa, Akita (A–C) and M. Takai, Kochi (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964761/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964779>
    dc:description "FIGURE 18. Scanning electron micrographs for Eremophylus hirtus (A−G) and P. nakagawai n. sp. (H−O). A, D, H. Left lateral habitus. B, I, J. Dorsal habitus. K. Ventral habitus. C. Corium. E, M. Thoracic pleura, left lateral view. F, N, O. Metatarsus. G, L. Apex of labium." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964779/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964823>
    dc:description "FIGURE 28. Scanning electron micrographs for Pityopsallus luridus from Yakutia, Russia (A−C), P. yasunagai (Vinokurov) (D–F, O), P. ermolenkoi (Kerzhner) (G–I, M), P. sakuraii n. sp. (J), P. vittatus (K, N) and P. nipponicus (Vinokurov) (L). A. Anterior body, dorsolateral view. B. Vestiture pattern on scutellum and anterior hemelytron. C–D, G–L. Male genital segment (pygophore), left lateral view. E. Same, caudal view. F. Apex of vesica. M–O. Pretarsal structure of metatarsus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964823/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964743>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Dorsal (A, C, F, H) and ventral (B, D, E, G, I) habitus images of Eremophylus spp. A–B. E. hirtus, female. C–D. E. nakagawai sp. n., male. E. Same, partly paler variant. F–G. Same, female. H–I. Same, paler variant." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964743/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964765>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Dorsal (A, E, C, F) and ventral (B, D) habitus images of Pityopsallus spp. A–B. P. maeharai n. sp., male. C–D. Same, female. E. P. sakuraii n. sp., holotype male. F. P. vittatus, female (from Yakutia, Russia)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964765/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964752>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Habitus images of living individuals of Japanese Europiella spp. A. E. artemisiae, male. B. E. decolor, male (pale variant). C. Same, female (pale variant). D. Same, female. E. E. lividella, female. F–G. E. isodonicola n. sp., male. H. Same, female. I. Same, 5th instar nymph. J. E. miyamotoi, female. K. Same, 5th instar nymph. L. E. nihonica n. sp., female." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964752/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964835>
    dc:description "FIGURE 30. Scanning electron micrographs for Psallus (Hylopsallus) castaneae (A−F), P. (H.) ramae n. sp. (G−M) and P. (H.) tonnaichanus (N−O). A, G, N. Left lateral habitus. B. Vestiture pattern on anterior thorax. C, H. Thoracic pleura, left lateral view. D, E, I, J, K, O. Male genital segment, left lateral view (J–K, O: clustered stiff setae). F, L, M. Metatarsus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5964835/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

